{
  "comment_text": {
    "snp4.15:3.4": "<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Osita</i> (and <i lang='pi' translate='no'>osāna</i> in the next line) convey both “occupy” and “end” in the sense of a place of rest at the end of a journey. ",
    "snp4.15:4.1": "Here, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>tveva</i> has a contrastive sense. ",
    "snp4.15:6.1": "Agreeing with Norman that this line is likely a reciter’s remark. However, I take <i lang='pi' translate='no'>tattha</i> as the locative of reference. “That topic” is the extraction of the dart, for which the remainder of the sutta gives practical guidelines. "
  },
